sg.edu.cs2103aug2015_w13_2j.commands

Class CommandHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • sg.edu.cs2103aug2015_w13_2j.commands.CommandHandler
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AddHandler, DeleteHandler, EditHandler, FilterHandler, HelpHandler, LoadHandler, MarkCompletedHandler, MarkImportantHandler, PopHandler, RedoHandler, SearchHandler, UndoHandler

    public abstract class CommandHandler
extends java.lang.Object
    Base abstract class inherited by all command handlers. Provides default methods to set and retrieve the name, syntax, flags, options and reserved keyword strings of the command handlers. Also provides a method to update Task objects from information contained within a Command object.
    Author:
    Zhu Chunqi

    • Constructor Detail

      • CommandHandler

        public CommandHandler(java.lang.String name,
                      java.lang.String syntax,
                      java.lang.String[] flags,
                      java.lang.String[] options,
                      java.lang.String[] reserved)
        Constructor for all CommandHandler objects. Stores the name, syntax, supported flags, supported options and reserved keyword strings of the CommandHandler. Each inheriting CommandHandler must provide valid parameters as the values are not initialized by default.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of this CommandHandler.
        syntax - Syntax required by this CommandHandler.
        flags - String array of flags supported and their descriptions.
        options - String array of options supported and their descriptions.
        reserved - Array of reserved keyword strings handled by this CommandHandler.

      • shouldDisplay

        public boolean shouldDisplay()
        Checks if this CommandHandler requires a display refresh after execution. Defaults to true for all CommandHandlers unless shouldDisplay() is explicitly overridden to return false.
        Returns:
